UID:film-independent-fiction-producing-lab-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260501T055827Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260504
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260505
SUMMARY:Deadline: Film Independent: Fiction Producing Lab 2026
DESCRIPTION:Two-week in-person LA lab for lead producers formally attached 
 to full-length\, live-action\, fiction feature films with a completed scri
 pt and director in place. Each Fellow is paired with a Creative Advisor\, 
 attends sessions with legal/financial/production experts\, and culminates 
 in a pitch session with established executives. Includes professional coac
 hing by Renee Freedman & Company (supported by The Harnisch Foundation). P
 roducing partners may apply as a team via a single application. Not eligib
 le: documentaries\, animation\, short films\, new media\, episodic project
 s. International applicants are welcome but Film Independent does not subs
 idise travel\, lodging or visa costs. International fellows are eligible f
 or the Dolby Institute Fellowship ($50K post-production grant utilising Do
 lby Vision and Atmos). Lab alums become eligible to apply to the Amplifier
  Fellowship for Black filmmakers ($30K unrestricted plus year-long support
 \; six fellows annually\; eligibility also via Project Involve\, Spirit Aw
 ards nominee\, or nomination by a colleague arts organisation). Notificati
 ons go out 3 to 4 weeks before the programme starts. Application fee: free
  for Filmmaker Pro members (1 waiver/year)\, $45 for Film Independent memb
 ers\, $65 for non-members. Non-member deadline 4 May 2026\; Film Independe
 nt member extension to 18 May 2026. Application materials: cover letter\, 
 artist statement\, complete feature-length screenplay\, logline and synops
 is\, bios of attached key cast/crew\, project status and history\, budget 
 top sheet and finance plan\, optional lookbook\, optional work sample or r
 ough cut. Sloan Producers Grant requires the applicant to be attached as p
 roducer with rights to the script and to submit a statement on how the pro
 ject fulfils the Sloan Foundation mission (public engagement with science)
 .\n\nOrganisation: Film Independent\nLocation: Los Angeles\, US (in-person
 \; international applicants welcome but no travel\, lodging or visa subsid
 y is provided)\nAward: No tuition for the Lab itself. Accepted fellows mus
 t join Film Independent at $105/year. Bundled fellowship pathways: Alfred 
 P. Sloan Producers Grant ($30\,000 to one Lab participant whose project ha
 s a scientific\, mathematical or technological theme or a leading scientis
 t/engineer/mathematician character\; documentaries and science fiction pro
 jects not eligible). Lab also opens access to bundled $10K Artist Developm
 ent fellowships (Cayton-Goldrich\, MPAC Hollywood Bureau\, Sony Music Visi
 on) for eligible fellows.\nDuration: 2 weeks intensive (October 2026)\n\nM
 ore: https://www.filmindependent.org/programs/artist-development/fiction-p
 roducing-lab/
URL:https://www.filmindependent.org/programs/artist-development/fiction-pro
 ducing-lab/
LOCATION:Los Angeles\, US (in-person\; international applicants welcome but
  no travel\, lodging or visa subsidy is provided)
END:VEVENT
